# npm-bundled transitive dependencies (minimatch, tar)
# These are internal to npm's own node_modules and only used during
# package installation, not at application runtime. They will be fixed
# when Node.js ships a release with updated npm.

# minimatch: DoS via crafted glob patterns (npm-internal)
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# tar: file overwrite via malicious archive (npm-internal)
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802

# Ubuntu base-image findings. These are in packages shipped by the
# ubuntu:24.04 base image (pinned by SHA in docker/Dockerfile.base) and
# get refreshed when the base image is rebuilt by the
# `Docker Base Image` workflow. Listing them here keeps the per-PR
# Trivy scan green between base-image rebuilds.

# linux-libc-dev: Linux kernel HEADER files only. The container shares
# the host kernel; these CVEs are not reachable from inside the image.
CVE-2026-23111
CVE-2026-23112
CVE-2026-23231
CVE-2025-68263
CVE-2026-22984
CVE-2026-23172
CVE-2026-31431
CVE-2026-43284
CVE-2026-43500
CVE-2026-46300
CVE-2026-46323
CVE-2026-46333
CVE-2026-47331
CVE-2026-47333

# openssl / libssl3t64: Heap use-after-free in PKCS7_verify(). Shipped
# by the ubuntu:24.04 base image; fix is in 3.0.13-0ubuntu3.11, which
# lands via a base-image rebuild. Compresso does not invoke PKCS7
# verification at runtime.
CVE-2026-45447

# packagekit / gir1.2-packagekitglib-1.0: system package-management
# daemon. Not invoked at runtime by the Compresso server; pulled in
# transitively by base image packages. Fix is in 1.2.8-2ubuntu1.5,
# which will land via a base-image rebuild.
CVE-2026-41651
